{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":936,"text":"Silicon Valley\nis obsessed with disruption,"},{"time":4560,"text":"but these days, the biggest disruptor\ndidn't come out of Silicon Valley."},{"time":9079,"text":"It came out of steel towns in Ohio,"},{"time":12280,"text":"rural communities in Pennsylvania,"},{"time":15600,"text":"the Panhandle in Florida."},{"time":19000,"text":"And this last US presidential election"},{"time":21960,"text":"was the mother of all disruptions."},{"time":25160,"text":"Once again, politics is personal."},{"time":29120,"text":"Millions of Americans\nbecame activists overnight,"},{"time":32560,"text":"pouring into the streets in record numbers"},{"time":35400,"text":"in record time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38680,"text":"The election has done\nto family holiday dinners"},{"time":41040,"text":"what Uber has done\nto New York City's taxi system."},{"time":45240,"text":"Couples have broken up\nand marriages disrupted."},{"time":50160,"text":"And the election\nis doing to my private life"},{"time":52280,"text":"what Amazon is doing to shopping malls."},{"time":54840,"text":"These days, the ACLU\nis on the front lines 24/7,"},{"time":60120,"text":"and even if I manage to sneak away\nfor a couple of miles on the treadmill,"},{"time":65239,"text":"any cardio benefit I get\nis instantly obliterated"},{"time":69080,"text":"when I read another presidential tweet\non the headline scroll."},{"time":74280,"text":"Even my secret pleasure"},{"time":76960,"text":"of studying the Italian painters"},{"time":79480,"text":"have been infected by politics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82720,"text":"Now, I study, even stalk, the old masters."},{"time":86280,"text":"This is my desk,"},{"time":87880,"text":"with a postcard exhibition"},{"time":89720,"text":"of some famous and obscure paintings"},{"time":91600,"text":"mostly from the Italian Renaissance."},{"time":94280,"text":"Now, art used to provide me\nwith a necessary break"},{"time":96760,"text":"from the hurly-burly of politics"},{"time":99080,"text":"in my daily work at the ACLU,"},{"time":101480,"text":"but not anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103560,"text":"I was at the Women's March\nin San Francisco"},{"time":105640,"text":"the day after inauguration,"},{"time":107200,"text":"and the crowd was chanting,\n\"This is what democracy looks like.\""},{"time":110280,"text":"\"This is what democracy looks like.\""},{"time":113560,"text":"And there I was holding my sign\nand my umbrella in the rain,"},{"time":117560,"text":"and I flashed on an old painting"},{"time":121400,"text":"that first captivated me many years ago."},{"time":124520,"text":"I struggled to remember\nthe different pieces"},{"time":127880,"text":"of an actual painting"},{"time":130240,"text":"of good and bad government."},{"time":133160,"text":"It was almost like the old master\nwas taunting me."},{"time":136320,"text":"You want to know\nwhat democracy looks like?"},{"time":138840,"text":"Go back and look at my frescoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141960,"text":"And so I did."},{"time":144160,"text":"In 1339, Ambrogio Lorenzetti\nfinished a monumental commission"},{"time":149960,"text":"in the governing council chamber\nof Siena's Palazzo Pubblico."},{"time":153800,"text":"It's a painting that speaks to us,\neven screams to us, today."},{"time":160480,"text":"\"Art is a lie that makes us\nrealize truth,\""},{"time":164280,"text":"Pablo Picasso once said."},{"time":166680,"text":"And as we search for the truth\nabout government,"},{"time":168960,"text":"we should keep Ambrogio's work,"},{"time":170880,"text":"not a lie but an allegory,\nin our collective mind's eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176560,"text":"During Lorenzetti's time,"},{"time":178000,"text":"the political legitimacy\nof Italian city-states"},{"time":181320,"text":"was often on very shaky ground."},{"time":183800,"text":"Siena was a republic,"},{"time":185680,"text":"but there had been enormous unrest"},{"time":187360,"text":"in the two decades\nleading up to the commission."},{"time":190240,"text":"Siena's political leaders,\nwho would literally govern"},{"time":193560,"text":"under the eyes\nof these allegorical figures,"},{"time":196760,"text":"were Lorenzetti's intended audience."},{"time":199720,"text":"He was cataloging the obligations"},{"time":201960,"text":"of the governing to the governed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206400,"text":"Now, you can spend years\nstudying these frescoes."},{"time":209440,"text":"Some scholars have."},{"time":211360,"text":"I'm hardly an art historian,"},{"time":213520,"text":"but I am passionate about art,"},{"time":216120,"text":"and a work this massive can overwhelm me."},{"time":218720,"text":"So first, I focus on the big stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223800,"text":"This is the allegory of good government."},{"time":227760,"text":"The majestic figure here in the middle"},{"time":230000,"text":"is dressed in Siena's colors"},{"time":232440,"text":"and he personifies the republic itself."},{"time":236200,"text":"Lorenzetti labels him \"Commune,\""},{"time":239280,"text":"and he's basically telling the Sienese"},{"time":241960,"text":"that they, and not a king or a tyrant,\nmust rule themselves."},{"time":247120,"text":"Now, surrounding Commune are his advisors."},{"time":253760,"text":"Justice is enthroned."},{"time":255880,"text":"She's looking up at the figure of wisdom,"},{"time":259040,"text":"who actually supports\nher scales of justice."},{"time":265000,"text":"Concord, or Harmony,"},{"time":267560,"text":"holds a string that comes\noff the scales of justice"},{"time":270720,"text":"that binds her to the citizens,"},{"time":272760,"text":"making them all\ncompatriots in the republic."},{"time":278200,"text":"And finally we see Peace."},{"time":279880,"text":"She looks chilled out,"},{"time":281360,"text":"like she's listening to Bob Marley."},{"time":283760,"text":"When good government rules,"},{"time":285760,"text":"Peace doesn't break a sweat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288240,"text":"Now, these are big images and big ideas,"},{"time":290680,"text":"but I really love the small stuff."},{"time":293480,"text":"Along another wall,"},{"time":294920,"text":"Lorenzetti illustrates\nthe effects of good government"},{"time":298280,"text":"on the real and everyday lives\nof ordinary people"},{"time":300680,"text":"with a series of delicious little details."},{"time":305440,"text":"In the countryside,\nthe hills are landscaped and farmed."},{"time":311280,"text":"Crops are being sown,\nhoed, reaped, milled, plowed,"},{"time":315000,"text":"all in one picture."},{"time":319000,"text":"Crops and livestock\nare being brought to market."},{"time":323480,"text":"In the city, builders raise a tower."},{"time":328400,"text":"People attend a law lecture,\na TED Talk of the 14th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335280,"text":"Schoolchildren play."},{"time":339040,"text":"Tradesmen thrive."},{"time":343000,"text":"Dancers larger than life dance with joy."},{"time":348400,"text":"And watching over the republic\nis the winged figure Security,"},{"time":352560,"text":"whose banner reads,"},{"time":354040,"text":"\"Everyone shall go forth\nfreely without fear.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":359240,"text":"Now, what's amazing\nabout these images from 800 years ago"},{"time":361960,"text":"is that they're familiar to us today."},{"time":364520,"text":"We see what democracy looks like."},{"time":366880,"text":"We experience the effects\nof good government in our lives,"},{"time":370320,"text":"just as Lorenzetti did in his life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374960,"text":"But it is the allegory of bad government"},{"time":377920,"text":"that has been haunting me\nsince November 9."},{"time":381280,"text":"It's badly damaged,"},{"time":382800,"text":"but it reads like today's newspapers."},{"time":385520,"text":"And ruling over bad government\nis not the Commune"},{"time":388480,"text":"but the Tyrant."},{"time":390640,"text":"He has horns, tusks, crossed eyes,"},{"time":393800,"text":"braided hair."},{"time":395360,"text":"He obviously spends\na lot of time on that hair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397800,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":398960,"text":"Justice now lies helpless at his feet,"},{"time":403280,"text":"shackled."},{"time":404600,"text":"Her scales have been severed."},{"time":407120,"text":"Justice is the key antagonist\nto the Tyrant,"},{"time":410120,"text":"and she's been taken out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412640,"text":"Now, surrounding the Tyrant,"},{"time":414040,"text":"Lorenzetti illustrates\nthe vices that animate bad government."},{"time":419280,"text":"Avarice is the old woman\nclutching the strongbox"},{"time":423000,"text":"and a fisherman's hook"},{"time":424720,"text":"to pull in her fortune."},{"time":429080,"text":"Vainglory carries a mirror,"},{"time":432120,"text":"and Lorenzetti warns us\nagainst narcissistic leaders"},{"time":435200,"text":"who are guided\nby their own ego and vanity."},{"time":439520,"text":"On the Tyrant's right is Cruelty."},{"time":447400,"text":"Treason, half lamb, half scorpion,"},{"time":450720,"text":"lulls us into a false sense of security"},{"time":453480,"text":"and then poisons a republic."},{"time":457000,"text":"Fraud, with the flighty wings of a bat."},{"time":465040,"text":"On the Tyrant's left, you see Division."},{"time":467920,"text":"She's dressed in Siena's colors."},{"time":470240,"text":"\"Si\" and \"No\" are painted on her body."},{"time":473720,"text":"She uses a carpenter's saw\nto chop her body in half."},{"time":481280,"text":"And Fury wields the weapons of the mob,"},{"time":484240,"text":"the stone and knife."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491280,"text":"In the remainder of the fresco,\nLorenzetti shows us"},{"time":493720,"text":"the inevitable effects of bad government."},{"time":496160,"text":"The civic ideals celebrated\nelsewhere in this room have failed us,"},{"time":499720,"text":"and we see it."},{"time":501280,"text":"The once beautiful city\nhas fallen to pieces,"},{"time":504040,"text":"the countryside barren,"},{"time":505880,"text":"the farms abandoned."},{"time":507440,"text":"Many are in flames."},{"time":510080,"text":"And in the sky above\nis not the winged figure Security,"},{"time":513960,"text":"but that of Fear, whose banner reads:"},{"time":517640,"text":"\"None shall pass along this road"},{"time":520679,"text":"without fear of death.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":525200,"text":"Now, the final image,\nthe most important one, really,"},{"time":527720,"text":"is one that Lorenzetti did not paint."},{"time":529560,"text":"It is of the viewer."},{"time":530840,"text":"Today, the audience\nfor Lorenzetti's frescoes"},{"time":533640,"text":"is not the governing but the governed,"},{"time":537120,"text":"the individual who stands\nin front of his allegories"},{"time":539960,"text":"and walks away with insight,"},{"time":542480,"text":"who heeds a call to action."},{"time":545520,"text":"Lorenzetti warns us\nthat we must recognize the shadows"},{"time":548240,"text":"of Avarice, Fraud, Division, even Tyranny"},{"time":552160,"text":"when they float\nacross our political landscape,"},{"time":554880,"text":"especially when those shadows are cast"},{"time":557720,"text":"by political leaders loudly claiming\nto be the voice of good government"},{"time":562400,"text":"and promising to make America great again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566880,"text":"And we must act."},{"time":569200,"text":"Democracy must not be a spectator sport."},{"time":571880,"text":"The right to protest,\nthe right to assemble freely,"},{"time":574320,"text":"the right to petition one's government,"},{"time":576240,"text":"these are not just rights."},{"time":578080,"text":"In the face of Avarice,\nFraud and Division,"},{"time":580600,"text":"these are obligations."},{"time":582960,"text":"We have to disrupt --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":584280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":589720,"text":"We have to disrupt our lives"},{"time":591920,"text":"so that we can disrupt"},{"time":593600,"text":"the amoral accretion of power"},{"time":596360,"text":"by those who would betray our values."},{"time":601040,"text":"We and we the people"},{"time":602960,"text":"must raise justice up"},{"time":604840,"text":"and must bring peace to our nation"},{"time":606800,"text":"and must come together in concord,"},{"time":609000,"text":"and we have a choice."},{"time":611800,"text":"We could either paint ourselves"},{"time":613360,"text":"into the worst nightmare\nof Lorenzetti's bad government,"},{"time":617320,"text":"or we can stay in the streets,"},{"time":620120,"text":"disruptive, messy, loud."},{"time":623680,"text":"That is what democracy looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":639400,"text":"Chris Anderson: First of all, wow."},{"time":641360,"text":"Obviously, many people passionately --"},{"time":643800,"text":"you spoke to many people\npassionately here."},{"time":645840,"text":"I'm sure there are other people here"},{"time":647600,"text":"who'd say, look, Trump was elected\nby 63 million people."},{"time":652320,"text":"He's far from perfect,"},{"time":653680,"text":"but he's trying to do\nwhat he was elected to do."},{"time":656680,"text":"Shouldn't you give him a chance?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":658720,"text":"Anthony Romero:\nI think we have to recognize"},{"time":660840,"text":"the legitimacy of him as president"},{"time":663640,"text":"versus the legitimacy of his policies."},{"time":666560,"text":"And when so many of the policies\nare contrary to fundamental values,"},{"time":672360,"text":"that we're all equal under the law,"},{"time":674320,"text":"that we're not judged by the color\nof our skin or the religion we worship,"},{"time":677920,"text":"we have to contest those values"},{"time":680680,"text":"even as we recognize and honor the fact"},{"time":682960,"text":"that our democracy rendered us a president\nwho is championing those values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688400,"text":"CA: And the ACLU isn't just\nthis force on the left, right?"},{"time":692240,"text":"You're making other arguments as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694680,"text":"AR: Well, you know,"},{"time":697320,"text":"very often we piss\neveryone off at one point."},{"time":699480,"text":"That's what we do."},{"time":701000,"text":"And we recently were taking stands"},{"time":703440,"text":"for why Ann Coulter needs\nto be able to speak at Berkeley,"},{"time":706800,"text":"and why Milo has free speech rights."},{"time":709240,"text":"And we even wrote a blog"},{"time":710840,"text":"that almost burnt the house down\namong some of our members,"},{"time":714520,"text":"unfortunately,\nwhen we talked about the fact"},{"time":716640,"text":"that even Donald Trump\nhas free speech rights as president,"},{"time":720120,"text":"and an effort to hold him accountable"},{"time":722200,"text":"for incitement of violence\nat his marches or his rallies"},{"time":726800,"text":"is unconstitutional and un-American."},{"time":730000,"text":"And when you put that statement out there"},{"time":732200,"text":"to a very frothy base"},{"time":733880,"text":"that always is very excited for you\nto fight Donald Trump,"},{"time":737200,"text":"and then you have a new one saying,\n\"Wait, these rights are for everybody,"},{"time":740720,"text":"even the president that we don't like.\""},{"time":742640,"text":"And that's our job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744240,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":747400,"text":"CA: Anthony, you spoke\nto so many of us so powerfully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Thank you so much. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751600,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}